text: Kamenny Yar () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kamennoyarsky Selsoviet, Chernoyarsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 988 as of 2010. There are 35 streets. == Geography == It is located on the Volga River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Chernoyarsky District
title: Kamenny Yar
